This paper deals with ontology-based data access, which is a topic closely related to databases (cs.DB). The paper also introduces a new temporal description logic (TQL) that extends OWL 2 QL, which is a language used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) for ontology modelling. The paper also discusses temporal conceptual modelling, which is a topic in logic (cs.LO) and software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper mentions first-order rewritability, which is a concept in programming languages (cs.PL).
